Changes per screen:
- StatelessWidget → ConsumerWidget
- StatefulWidget → ConsumerStatefulWidget
- UserManager.instance.x → ref.watch(userProvider)
- CartManager.instance.x → ref.watch(cartProvider)
- WishlistManager.instance.x → ref.watch(wishlistProvider)
- Navigator.push() → context.go() or context.push()
- Run flutter analyze after each screen batch, fix all errors

### ⏳ TASK 9 — Offline Caching
ProductRepository:
- After every Firestore fetch → save results to SQLite
- On Firestore failure (no internet) → load from SQLite cache
- Add cached_at timestamp column to SQLite
- Cache expires after 30 minutes
- If cache is expired and no internet → show stale data with warning

CartRepository:
- Always write to SQLite first (instant, no waiting)
- Sync to Firestore in background when online
- On app start → load from SQLite immediately (fast)
- Merge with Firestore version if conflict exists

